{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-5","id":"msg_011CcsSffHz339dbgZUJJ1fU","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The 3-node Elasticsearch cluster is deployed and healthy in the `elasticsearch` namespace, using only native Kubernetes resources:\n\n- **StatefulSet `es`** (3 replicas, `docker.elastic.co/elasticsearch/elasticsearch:8.11.1`), each node Ready and holding its own PVC.\n- **Service `es-http`** (ClusterIP, port 9200) for client access; **headless Service `es-transport`** (port 9300) for discovery/cluster formation.\n- **ConfigMap `es-config`** supplies `elasticsearch.yml` wiring up the existing `es-http-tls` secret for both HTTP and transport TLS (transport uses `verification_mode: certificate` since the cert's SAN only covers single-label service names, not per-pod hostnames).\n- **PDB `es-pdb`** allows at most 1 unavailable node.\n- The `elastic` user password is bootstrapped from the existing `elastic-password` secret via the `ELASTIC_PASSWORD` env var (using the legacy bootstrap-password keystore mechanism, since explicit TLS config disables 8.x's auto-configuration flow).\n\nVerified: cluster status is `green` with 3 nodes/3 data nodes, and from a separate pod (`curl-test`) I confirmed HTTPS reachability through `es-http.elasticsearch.svc.cluster.local:9200`, plus a successful write + read of a test document (cleaned up afterward)."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":835,"cache_read_input_tokens":62829,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":835},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"2675a6ed-3d35-4757-ba40-64cdef58e386","uuid":"59293e94-4446-49a7-aaee-994c362edf7e","request_id":"req_011CcsSfe3pSbp6nSy3V9mDF"}
